The paper deals with predicting the popularity of online videos, which is a topic related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM). The use of deep neural networks and scene dynamics’ metrics also suggests a connection to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of social features, which could fall under social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the use of Support Vector Regression and Gaussian radial basis functions suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
